review_blob: On tap at Brothers Beer Bistro. Great dark malt, roasted cereal. I got lots of grassy/herbaceous notes with very small citrus hops. Overall I thought the beer was well done but not the brewerys best.
Great beer from an awesome Brewery. Balance beer for 10.2%. Great charred/roast notes on both palate and nose.
Had it both in bottle and on tap. Great subtle notes of bret but the spice makes this a great beer to pair with food. Very versatile.
beer_name: Cuve Spiced Ale Aged in Bourbon Barrels

review_blob: This beer was a surprise. I guess I didnt read the deScription of the flavors but the Sour Cherry notes were very unexpected but awesome. Tons of red fruit acidity that helped cut the rich dark stout. Think burnt toast with jam on it.
beer_name: Sawdust City X Bar Hop Blood of Cthulhu

review_blob: Love the tropical fruit notes on the aroma. Great hop presence without being overwhelming. High alcohol but very balanced.
beer_name: Nickel Brook / Sawdust City 11/05 2014 Triple IPA
